semi-style.description:
Description

This rule reports line terminators around semicolons.

This rule has an option.

{
    "semi-style": ["error", "last"],
}

- "last"(Default) enforces that semicolons are at the end of statements.
- "first"enforces that semicolons are at the beginning of statements. Semicolons offorloop heads (for(a;b;c){}) should be at the end of lines even if you use this option.

Examples ofincorrectcode for this rule with"last"option:

/*eslint semi-style: ["error", "last"]*/

foo()
;[1, 2, 3].forEach(bar)

for (
    var i = 0
    ; i < 10
    ; ++i
) {
    foo()
}

class C {
    static {
        foo()
        ;bar()
    }
}

Examples ofcorrectcode for this rule with"last"option:

/*eslint semi-style: ["error", "last"]*/

foo();
[1, 2, 3].forEach(bar)

for (
    var i = 0;
    i < 10;
    ++i
) {
    foo()
}

class C {
    static {
        foo();
        bar()
    }
}

Examples ofincorrectcode for this rule with"first"option:

/*eslint semi-style: ["error", "first"]*/

foo();
[1, 2, 3].forEach(bar)

for (
    var i = 0
    ; i < 10
    ; ++i
) {
    foo()
}

class C {
    static {
        foo();
        bar()
    }
}

Examples ofcorrectcode for this rule with"first"option:

/*eslint semi-style: ["error", "first"]*/

foo()
;[1, 2, 3].forEach(bar)

for (
    var i = 0;
    i < 10;
    ++i
) {
    foo()
}

class C {
    static {
        foo()
        ;bar()
    }
}
